<eesti>Elektriohutusseadus </eesti>
<inglise>Electrical Safety Act </inglise>
<eesti>Vastu v&otilde;etud 23. veebruaril 1999. a, </eesti>
<inglise>Passed 23 February 1999, </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 1999, 29, 403), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT* I 1999, 29, 403), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 1. mail 1999. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 1 May 1999. </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab elektriseadmete, -paigaldiste ja -t&ouml;&ouml;de ning elektromagnetilise &uuml;hilduvuse &uuml;ldn&otilde;uded ning nende n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise &uuml;le riikliku j&auml;relevalve teostamise korra. </eesti>
<inglise>This Act provides the general requirements for electrical equipment, electrical installations, electrical work and electromagnetic compatibility, and the procedure for the exercise of state supervision over compliance with such requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektriseade ja elektripaigaldis </eesti>
<inglise>Electrical equipment and electrical installation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektriseade k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on elektrienergia tootmiseks, muundamiseks, edastamiseks, jaotamiseks v&otilde;i kasutamiseks m&otilde;eldud elektrilisi v&otilde;i elektroonilisi komponente sisaldav seade v&otilde;i tarvik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, electrical equipment is equipment or accessories which are intended to produce, transform, transmit, distribute or use electric power and which contain electrical or electronic components. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elektripaigaldis k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on elektriseadmete, -juhtide ja -tarvikute paigaldatud talitluslik kogum. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, electrical installation is an installed operational assembly of electrical equipment, conductors or accessories. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektriohutusn&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Electrical safety requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektriohutusn&otilde;uded k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on tehnilised ja administratiivsed n&otilde;uded, mille eesm&auml;rk on tagada vajalik elektriohutustase. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, electrical safety requirements are technical and administrative requirements the purpose of which is to ensure the necessary level of electrical safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elektriseadet ja -paigaldist tuleb kavandada, valmistada, paigaldada, kasutada, hooldada, remontida, &uuml;mber ehitada, katsetada ja kontrollida nii, et see: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Electrical equipment and electrical installations shall be designed, manufactured, installed, used, maintained, repaired, reconstructed, tested and inspected such that the equipment or installations: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ei ohustaks elu, tervist, vara ega keskkonda; </eesti>
<inglise>1) do not endanger life, health, property or the environment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ei tekitaks elektrilisi ega elektromagnetilisi h&auml;ireid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) do not cause electrical or electromagnetic disturbances; </inglise>
<eesti>3) oleks h&auml;irekindel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) have an intrinsic immunity to electromagnetic disturbances. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eri elektriseadmetele ja -paigaldistele esitatavad elektriohutusn&otilde;uded kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Electrical safety requirements for different electrical equipment and electrical installations shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Elektrit&ouml;&ouml;d </eesti>
<inglise>Electrical Work </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektrit&ouml;&ouml; </eesti>
<inglise>Electrical work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektrit&ouml;&ouml; on elektriseadme remontimine ja hooldamine ning elektripaigaldise projekteerimine, ehitamine, kontrollimine, katsetamine, remontimine ja hooldamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Electrical work is the repair or maintenance of electrical equipment, or the design, construction, inspection, testing, repair or maintenance of electrical installations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uded ei laiene elektripaigaldise k&auml;idule, kui tegemist ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud paigaldise k&auml;iduga ega k&auml;iduteenuse osutamisega teise isiku valduses olevas paigaldises. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements provided for in this Chapter do not extend to operation of electrical installations, except for operation of installations specified in subsection 9 (2) of this Act and provision of operation services in an installation which is in the possession of another person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elektrit&ouml;id tegev ettev&otilde;tja peab esitama Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonile teatise elektrit&ouml;&ouml;dega tegelema hakkamisel, esitatavate andmete muutumisel ja perioodiliselt igal aastal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A contractor performing electrical work shall submit a notice to the Technical Inspectorate upon commencement of electrical work, upon any change in the submitted information, and regularly every year. </inglise>
<eesti>Teatise esitamine ei ole n&otilde;utav lihtsamate elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>The submission of a notice is not required in the case of uncomplicated electrical work. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud lihtsamate elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de loetelu, teatises esitatavate andmete loetelu ja teatise esitamise kord kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The list of uncomplicated electrical works specified in subsection (3) of this section, the list of information to be submitted in a notice and the procedure for submission of notices shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektrit&ouml;id juhtiv isik </eesti>
<inglise>Person in charge of electrical work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektrit&ouml;id peab juhtima vastavat p&auml;devustunnistust omav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who is in charge of electrical work shall hold a corresponding certificate of competency. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektrit&ouml;id juhtiva isiku olemasolu ei ole n&otilde;utav k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 4 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud lihtsamate elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of uncomplicated electrical work specified in subsection 4 (3) of this Act there is no requirement for a person to be in charge of electrical work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;devustunnistuse saamise eelduseks olevad n&otilde;uded eri elektrit&ouml;id juhtivate isikute eriharidusele, t&ouml;&ouml;kogemusele ja elektriohutusn&otilde;uete tundmisele, samuti p&auml;devuse hindamise kord kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The prerequisites for persons in charge of different electrical works who wish to obtain a certificate of competency with regard to their level of professional education, work experience and expertise in electrical safety requirements, and the procedure for the assessment of their competence shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isiku vastavust k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud n&otilde;uetele hindab ja p&auml;devustunnistuse v&auml;ljastab selleks volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The compliance of persons with the prerequisites specified in subsection (2) of this section shall be assessed, and certificates of competency shall be issued by attestation bodies approved for such purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Elektrit&ouml;id juhtiv isik peab tagama, et: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Persons in charge of electrical work shall ensure that: </inglise>
<eesti>1) elektrit&ouml;&ouml;del j&auml;rgitakse elektriohutusn&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) electrical safety requirements are observed in the course of electrical work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) elektrit&ouml;id teostab nendeks t&ouml;&ouml;deks piisavat elektriohutusalast ettevalmistust omav isik; </eesti>
<inglise>2) electrical work is performed by persons whose training in electrical safety is sufficient for the performance of such work; </inglise>
<eesti>3) elektrit&ouml;&ouml; tegijat juhendatakse k&uuml;llaldaselt &uuml;lesannete n&otilde;uetekohaseks t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) persons who perform electrical work are adequately instructed for the proper performance of their duties; </inglise>
<eesti>4) elektrit&ouml;&ouml; tegija k&auml;sutuses on n&otilde;utav dokumentatsioon ja t&ouml;&ouml;de ohutuks teostamiseks vajalikud vahendid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons who perform electrical work have at their disposal the required documentation and necessary means for the safe performance of such work; </inglise>
<eesti>5) n&otilde;utav dokumentatsioon koostatakse ja esitatakse &otilde;igeaegselt. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the required documentation is prepared and submitted in good time. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Elektrit&ouml;id juhtiv isik peab olema k&auml;ttesaadav ohutuse tagamiseks ja j&auml;relevalvetoimingute l&auml;biviimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The person in charge of electrical work shall be available in order to ensure safety or perform supervisory operations. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Elektriseadmed </eesti>
<inglise>Electrical Equipment </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded elektriseadme tarnimisel </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for supply of electrical equipment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Keelatud on importida, m&uuml;&uuml;a v&otilde;i muul viisil Eestis kasutamiseks teisele isikule &uuml;le anda elektriseadet, mis ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) It is prohibited to import or sell electrical equipment, or to transfer electrical equipment to another person in any other manner for use in Estonia, if the electrical equipment does not comply with the requirements of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elektriseadme valmistaja v&otilde;i importija peab olema v&otilde;imeline t&otilde;endama, et elektriseadmena Eestis kasutamiseks toodetud v&otilde;i imporditud seade vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The manufacturer or importer of electrical equipment shall be able to prove that equipment which is produced or imported for use in Estonia as electrical equipment complies with the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui valmistajat v&otilde;i importijat pole v&otilde;imalik tuvastada, peab isik, kes paigaldab, m&uuml;&uuml;b v&otilde;i muul viisil annab teisele isikule &uuml;le elektriseadme Eestis kasutamiseks, olema v&otilde;imeline t&otilde;endama, et seade vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>If identification of the manufacturer or importer is impossible, the person who installs or sells electrical equipment, or transfers electrical equipment to another person in any other manner for use in Estonia shall be able to prove that such electrical equipment complies with the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elektriseadmete loetelu, mille m&uuml;&uuml;mise, importimise v&otilde;i muul viisil teisele isikule elektriseadmena Eestis kasutamiseks &uuml;leandmise puhul on n&otilde;utav nende seadmete eelnev n&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamine ja t&otilde;endamine selleks tegevuseks volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutuse poolt, kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The list of electrical equipment the sale, import or transfer of which to another person in any other manner for use in Estonia as electrical equipment requires prior assessment and attestation of conformity by attestation bodies approved for such purpose shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Kasutatud elektriseadme m&uuml;&uuml;k ja &uuml;leandmine </eesti>
<inglise>Sale and transfer of second-hand electrical equipment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kasutatud elektriseadme m&uuml;&uuml;ja v&otilde;i kasutusse andja peab enne selle m&uuml;&uuml;ki v&otilde;i muul viisil teisele isikule elektriseadmena Eestis kasutamiseks &uuml;leandmist ja elektriseadme remontija enne selle remondij&auml;rgset &uuml;leandmist veenduma, et seade vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons who sell or grant use of second-hand electrical equipment shall verify compliance thereof with the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof before sale of equipment or transfer thereof to another person in any other manner for use in Estonia as electrical equipment; persons who repair electrical equipment shall verify compliance of equipment with the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof after repair before transfer of equipment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juhul kui remontija tuvastab, et remonditud seade ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele, peab ta sellest teatama isikule, kellele seade p&auml;rast remonti &uuml;le antakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who repairs electrical equipment and establishes that the repaired equipment does not comply with the requirements of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof is required to notify the person to whom the equipment is transferred after repair that the equipment does not comply with the requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Elektripaigaldised </eesti>
<inglise>Electrical Installations </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektripaigaldise kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of electrical installations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektripaigaldis v&otilde;i selle osa loetakse kasutuselev&otilde;etuks hetkest, mil elektripaigaldis v&otilde;i selle osa pingestatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An electrical installation or a part thereof is deemed to be taken into service as of the moment of energising the electrical installation or a part thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elektripaigaldise kasutuselev&otilde;tuks ei loeta j&auml;relevalve all toimuvat pingestamist, mis on vajalik seadmestiku katsetamiseks v&otilde;i kasutuselev&otilde;tukontrolli teostamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Energising under supervision necessary for the testing, or the conduct of inspection before taking into service of a plant is deemed not to be the taking into service. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Keelatud on kasutada v&otilde;i kasutamise eesm&auml;rgil paigaldada elektriseadet v&otilde;i -paigaldist, mis ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Use or installation for the purpose of use of electrical equipment or installations which do not comply with the requirements of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektripaigaldise kasutuselev&otilde;tukontroll ja n&otilde;uetekohasuse t&otilde;endamine </eesti>
<inglise>Inspection before taking into service and attestation of conformity of electrical installations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ehitatud v&otilde;i &uuml;mberehitatud elektripaigaldise v&otilde;i selle osa v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta kasutusele p&auml;rast paigaldises elektrit&ouml;id teinud ettev&otilde;tja poolt korraldatud kasutuselev&otilde;tukontrolli, mille k&auml;igus veendutakse, et paigaldis vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Constructed or reconstructed electrical installations or parts thereof may be taken into service after the contractor who performs the electrical work in the installation has organised an inspection to verify the compliance of the installation with the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elektripaigaldisi, mille kasutamisega kaasnevad k&otilde;rgemad ohud, ei tohi v&otilde;tta kasutusele enne nende n&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamist ja t&otilde;endamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Electrical installations the use of which involves increased danger shall not be taken into service before the assessment and attestation of their conformity. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud n&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamisel ja t&otilde;endamisel hinnatakse paigaldise ning selle ehitamise v&otilde;i &uuml;mberehitamise ja kasutuselev&otilde;tukontrolli vastavust elektriohutusn&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the assessment and attestation of conformity specified in subsection (2) of this section, an installation, the construction or reconstruction thereof, and the inspection of the installation before taking into service, are assessed for their conformity. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud elektripaigaldiste loetelu, mille puhul n&otilde;uetekohasust hindab ja t&otilde;endab volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus, ja loetelu, mille puhul n&otilde;uetekohasust hindab ja t&otilde;endab lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja, kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The list of electrical installations specified in subsection (2) of this section the conformity of which is assessed and attested by approved attestation bodies, and the list of installations the conformity of which is assessed and attested by electrical contractors with the right to perform additional inspections shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Teatis elektripaigaldise kasutuselev&otilde;tu kohta ja elektripaigaldiste register </eesti>
<inglise>Notice concerning taking into service of electrical installation and electrical installations register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ehitatud v&otilde;i &uuml;mberehitatud elektripaigaldise esmakordse kasutuselev&otilde;tu kohta peab elektripaigaldise valdaja esitama teatise sellele v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjale v&otilde;i elektrienergia tootjale, kelle tegevuspiirkonnas elektripaigaldis asub. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A possessor of a constructed or reconstructed electrical installation shall submit a notice concerning the taking into service of the installation for the first time to the network operator or the producer of electric power within whose territory the electrical installation is located. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud elektripaigaldise kohta, mille suhtes viidi l&auml;bi n&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamine, peab vastavalt kas volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus v&otilde;i lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja esitama teatise Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An approved attestation body or an electrical contractor with the right to perform additional inspections, correspondingly, shall submit a notice to the Technical Inspectorate concerning an electrical installation specified in subsection 9 (2) of this Act with regard to which an assessment of conformity was performed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjad ja elektrienergia tootjad peavad oma tegevuspiirkonnas asuvate elektripaigaldiste registrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Network operators and producers of electric power shall maintain registers of electrical installations located within their territories. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 etten&auml;htud teatise esitamise ja l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud registrite pidamise kord kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The procedure for the submission of notices prescribed in subsections (1) or (2) of this section and for the maintenance of registers specified in subsection (3) of this section shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektripaigaldise k&auml;it ja k&auml;idukorraldaja </eesti>
<inglise>Operation of electrical installation and person in control of electrical installation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektripaigaldise k&auml;it on elektripaigaldise igap&auml;evase k&auml;igus hoidmisega seotud tegevus nagu kasutamine, kontrollimine ja hooldamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Operation of an electrical installation is the activities related to the day-to-day running of electrical installations, such as use, inspection and maintenance of installations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;idukorraldaja on elektripaigaldise k&auml;itu vahetult korraldav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person in control of an electrical installation is the person who directly organises the operation of the electrical installation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Igas elektripaigaldises peab paigaldise valdaja tagama k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete, sealhulgas k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 7 ja 8 s&auml;testatud k&auml;idukorraldaja &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In each electrical installation, the possessor of the installation shall ensure compliance with the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the bases thereof, including the performance of the duties of the person in control of electrical installations provided for in subsections (7) and (8) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Elektripaigaldise valdaja v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata elektripaigaldisele k&auml;idukorraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The possessor of an electrical installation may appoint a person in control of the electrical installation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud elektripaigaldisele peab selle valdaja m&auml;&auml;rama k&auml;idukorraldaja, kelleks peab olema k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 5 nimetatud p&auml;devustunnistust omav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The possessor of an electrical installation specified in subsection 9 (2) of this Act shall appoint a person in control of the electrical installation who shall hold a certificate of competency specified in &sect; 5 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;idukorraldaja m&auml;&auml;ramisel l&auml;hevad talle &uuml;le k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Upon the appointment of a person in control of an electrical installation, the duties specified in subsection (3) of this section transfer to such person. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektripaigaldise valdaja peab tagama k&auml;idukorraldajale v&otilde;imaluse t&auml;ita k&otilde;iki k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>The possessor of an electrical installation shall ensure that the person in control of the electrical installation has the means to comply with all the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;idukorraldaja &uuml;lesanne on elektripaigaldise k&auml;idul tagada, et: </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Upon the operation of an electrical installation, the duty of the person in control of the electrical installation is to ensure that: </inglise>
<eesti>1) j&auml;rgitakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof are observed; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ei kasutata elektriseadet ja -paigaldist, mis ei vasta elektriohutusn&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) electrical equipment or electrical installations which do not conform to electrical safety requirements are not used; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;id teostab nendeks t&ouml;&ouml;deks piisavat elektriohutusalast ettevalmistust omav isik; </eesti>
<inglise>3) work is performed by persons whose training in electrical safety is sufficient for such work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml; tegijat juhendatakse k&uuml;llaldaselt &uuml;lesannete n&otilde;uetekohaseks t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons who perform work are adequately instructed for the proper performance of their duties; </inglise>
<eesti>5) elektripaigaldises on t&ouml;&ouml; tegija k&auml;sutuses vajalik dokumentatsioon ja t&ouml;&ouml;de ohutuks teostamiseks vajalikud vahendid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) persons who perform work in the electrical installation have the necessary documentation and means for the safe performance of such work at their disposal; </inglise>
<eesti>6) korrap&auml;rast hooldust n&otilde;udva elektripaigaldise v&otilde;i -seadme kohta on hoolduskava ning seda j&auml;rgitakse; </eesti>
<inglise>6) maintenance schedules exist for electrical installations and electrical equipment which require periodical maintenance, and that such schedules are observed; </inglise>
<eesti>7) elektripaigaldise korralist kontrolli teostatakse &otilde;igeaegselt; </eesti>
<inglise>7) regular inspections of the electrical installation are performed in good time; </inglise>
<eesti>8) elule, tervisele v&otilde;i varale ohu ilmnemisel peatatakse elektriseadme v&otilde;i -paigaldise kasutamine v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; kuni ohu m&ouml;&ouml;dumise v&otilde;i k&otilde;rvaldamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>8) in the case of a danger to life, health or property, the use or operation of the electrical equipment or electrical installation is suspended until the danger ceases to exist or is eliminated. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) K&auml;idukorraldaja peab olema k&auml;ttesaadav ohutuse tagamiseks ja j&auml;relevalvetoimingute l&auml;biviimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The person in control of an electrical installation shall be available in order to ensure safety and perform supervisory acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektripaigaldise korraline kontroll </eesti>
<inglise>Regular inspection of electrical installation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektripaigaldise elektriohutusalase korralise kontrolli l&auml;biviimise peab korraldama elektripaigaldise valdaja v&otilde;i tema m&auml;&auml;ratud k&auml;idukorraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The performance of regular inspections of the electrical safety of an electrical installation shall be organised by the possessor of the electrical installation or the person in control of the electrical installation appointed by the possessor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud elektripaigaldistes teostab korralist kontrolli vastavalt kas volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus v&otilde;i lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Regular inspections of electrical installations specified in subsection 9 (2) of this Act shall be performed by approved attestation bodies or electrical contractors with the right to perform additional inspections, correspondingly. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elektripaigaldiste korralise kontrolli l&auml;biviimise kord kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for the performance of regular inspections of electrical installations shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economics. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>H&auml;ired, ohud ja &uuml;mberehitused </eesti>
<inglise>Disturbances, Dangers and Reconstruction </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>H&auml;ired ja ohud </eesti>
<inglise>Disturbances and dangers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhul kui elektripaigaldis p&otilde;hjustab h&auml;ireid v&otilde;i ohtu teisele elektripaigaldisele v&otilde;i selle k&auml;idule v&otilde;i teise paigaldise vahendusel kolmandale elektripaigaldisele, kusjuures nii h&auml;iriv kui h&auml;iritav elektripaigaldis on n&otilde;uetekohase tehnilise lahendusega ja vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 3 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele, peab hiljem valminud elektripaigaldise omanik tegema oma elektripaigaldises h&auml;irete ja ohu v&auml;ltimiseks vajalikud &uuml;mberehitust&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an electrical installation causes disturbances or danger to another electrical installation or the operation thereof, or to a third electrical installation through another installation, and both the disturbing and the disturbed electrical installation have proper technical solutions and comply with the requirements provided for in &sect; 3 of this section, the owner of the electrical installation which was completed later shall perform the reconstruction work in the installation necessary for the prevention of disturbances and danger. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juhul kui h&auml;irete v&otilde;i ohu k&otilde;rvaldamine on lihtsam ja odavam varem valminud elektripaigaldise tehnilist struktuuri muutes v&otilde;i t&auml;iendades ning seda on v&otilde;imalik teha paigaldise t&ouml;&ouml;d oluliselt h&auml;irimata, peab varem valminud paigaldise omanik tegema oma paigaldises h&auml;irete ja ohu v&auml;ltimiseks vajalikud &uuml;mberehitust&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the elimination of disturbances or danger is less complicated or less expensive by altering or supplementing the technical structure of the electrical installation which was completed earlier, and such alteration or supplementation can be made without significant disturbance to the operation of the installation, the owner of the installation which was completed earlier shall perform the reconstruction work in the installation necessary for the prevention of disturbances and danger. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kahest elektripaigaldisest v&otilde;i selle osast loetakse hiljem valminuks see, mis on liidetud elektriv&otilde;rguga hiljem. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Of two electrical installations, the electrical installation, or a part thereof which is connected to a power network later than the other electrical installation or a part thereof is deemed to be completed later. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;mberehitusega kaasnevad kulud </eesti>
<inglise>Costs related to reconstruction </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 13 s&auml;testatud juhtudel peab hiljem valminud elektripaigaldise omanik h&uuml;vitama varem valminud paigaldise omanikule &uuml;mberehitusega tekkinud kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>In the cases provided for in &sect; 13 of this Act, the owner of the electrical installation which was completed later shall compensate the costs related to the reconstruction of the installation which was completed earlier to the owner of the installation. </inglise>
<eesti>Kulude m&auml;&auml;ramisel tuleb arvestada &uuml;mberehituse tulemusena varem valminud paigaldise omanikule paigaldise toimev&otilde;ime v&otilde;i k&auml;idukulude suuruse muutumisest tekkinud kasu v&otilde;i kahju. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon determination of costs, the profit or loss which the owner of the installation which was completed earlier incurs as a result of reconstruction due to change in the operational capacity or the amount of operating expenses of the installation shall be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise &uuml;le teostab riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon (edaspidi inspektsioon). </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision over compliance with the requirements provided for in this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof shall be exercised by the Technical Inspectorate (hereinafter Inspectorate). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsiooni elektriohutusj&auml;relevalvealane p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of Inspectorate in supervision of electrical safety </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsiooni p&auml;devusse kuulub: </eesti>
<inglise>The competence of the Inspectorate includes: </inglise>
<eesti>1) elektriseadmete ja -paigaldiste elektriohutusn&otilde;uetele vastavuse j&auml;relevalve; </eesti>
<inglise>1) supervision of compliance of electrical equipment and electrical installations with electrical safety requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>2) elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele vastavuse j&auml;relevalve; </eesti>
<inglise>2) supervision of compliance of electrical work with the requirements of this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>3) elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tjale k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 22 s&auml;testatud lisakontrolli&otilde;iguse andmine ja t&uuml;histamine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) grant and revocation of the right to perform the additional inspections specified in &sect; 22 of this Act to electrical contractors; </inglise>
<eesti>4) j&auml;relevalve volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutuse ja lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja elektriohutusalase hindamis-, t&otilde;endamis- ja kontrollitegevuse &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>4) supervision of the assessment, attestation and inspection activities which the approved attestation bodies and electrical contractors with the right to perform additional inspection carry out with regard to electrical safety; </inglise>
<eesti>5) elektri&otilde;nnetuste tekkep&otilde;hjuste v&auml;ljaselgitamine. </eesti>
<inglise>5) establishment of the causes of accidents related to electricity. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsiooni &otilde;igused ja kohustused elektriohutusj&auml;relevalve teostamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and duties of Inspectorate upon exercise of supervision over electrical safety </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus saada riigiasutustelt elektriohutusalase j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks vajalikku teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Inspectorate has the right to obtain information necessary for the exercise of supervision over electrical safety from state agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon teeb majandusministrile ettepaneku volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutuse volituste ulatuse piiramiseks v&otilde;i volituste kehtetuks tunnistamiseks, kui volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus ei vasta talle esitatavatele k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i ei t&auml;ida oma hindamis- ja t&otilde;endamistegevuses talle esitatavaid n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Inspectorate makes proposals to the Minister of Economic Affairs for the restriction of the extent of the authority or revocation of the authority of an approved attestation body if the approved attestation body does not comply with the requirements established for the body by this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof or if the assessment or attestation activities of the attestation body do not comply with the requirements established for the body. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsiooni elektriohutusalast j&auml;relevalvet teostaval ametnikul on k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel inspektsiooni p&auml;devusse kuuluvates k&uuml;simustes &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Officials of the Inspectorate exercising supervision over electrical safety have the right, with regard to the issues within the competence of the Inspectorate on the basis of this Act, to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) siseneda kontrollimise eesm&auml;rgil elektriseadmete ja -paigaldiste valmistamis-, paigaldus-, remondi-, hooldus-, ladustamis- ja m&uuml;&uuml;gikohale ning elektripaigaldiste asukohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) enter, for the purpose of inspection, the places of manufacture, installation, repair, maintenance, storage or sale of electrical equipment or electrical installations, and the locations of electrical installations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) saada elektriseadme v&otilde;i -paigaldise valdajalt, elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tjalt, elektriseadme valmistajalt, elektriseadme importijalt, volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutuselt v&otilde;i lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tjalt j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks vajalikku teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) obtain information necessary for the exercise of supervision from the possessors of electrical equipment or electrical installations, electrical contractors, manufacturers or importers of electrical equipment, approved attestation bodies and electrical contractors with the right to perform additional inspections; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teha ettekirjutusi k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete rikkumise l&otilde;petamiseks, sealhulgas n&otilde;uda k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele mittevastava elektriseadme v&otilde;i -paigaldise kasutamise peatamist, m&auml;&auml;rates &uuml;htlasi t&auml;htaja ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) issue precepts for termination of violations of the requirements of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof, including the right to demand suspension of the use of electrical equipment or electrical installations which do not comply with the requirements of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof, and set a term for the compliance with the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsiooni peadirektoril ja tema aset&auml;itjal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel inspektsiooni p&auml;devusse kuuluvates k&uuml;simustes &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Director General of the Inspectorate or his or her deputy have the right, with regard to the issues within the competence of the Inspectorate on the basis of this Act, to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kohustada seadme valmistajat, importijat v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;jat teatama avalikkusele seadmega seotud ohtudest v&otilde;i edastada selline teade valmistaja, importija v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;ja kulul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) require the manufacturers, importers or sellers of equipment to notify the public of dangers relating to the equipment, or to communicate such information at the expense of the manufacturer, importer or seller; </inglise>
<eesti>2) keelata f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku tegutsemine k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 5 nimetatud elektrit&ouml;id juhtiva isikuna, kui see isik korduvalt rikub k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid, olenevalt rikkumise raskusastmest kuni kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) prohibit a natural person from acting as a person in charge of electrical work specified in &sect; 5 of this Act if the person repeatedly violates the requirements of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof for up to three years depending on the severity of the violation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Inspektsiooni elektriohutusalast j&auml;relevalvet teostav ametnik on kohustatud oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel esitama ametit&otilde;endi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the performance of their duties, officials of the Inspectorate exercising supervision over electrical safety are required to present identification. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Inspektsiooni elektriohutusalast j&auml;relevalvet teostav ametnik on kohustatud tagama talle j&auml;relevalve teostamisel teatavaks saanud &auml;ri- ja tehnikaalase teabe saladuses hoidmise, kui seadused ei n&auml;e ette selle avaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Officials of the Inspectorate exercising supervision over electrical safety are required to ensure that the confidentiality of business and technical information which became known to them in the course of exercising supervision is maintained, unless the disclosure of such information is prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Katseeksemplaride saamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to obtain equipment samples </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsiooni elektriohutusj&auml;relevalvet teostaval ametnikul on &otilde;igus tasu eest v&otilde;tta elektriseadme importijalt, valmistajalt v&otilde;i muul viisil Eestis kasutamiseks &uuml;leandjalt vajalik kogus elektriseadmeid katseeksemplarideks, tuvastamaks nende vastavust elektriohutusn&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to establish the compliance of electrical equipment with electrical safety requirements, the officials of the Inspectorate exercising supervision over electrical safety have the right to take equipment samples for remuneration and in the necessary quantities from the importers or manufacturers of electrical equipment and from persons who transfer electrical equipment in any other manner for use in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib tellida elektriseadme ohutuse kontrollimiseks hindamisteenuse volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutuselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of inspection of the safety of electrical equipment, the Inspectorate may order assessment services from approved attestation bodies. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui tuvastatakse elektriseadme mittevastavus elektriohutusn&otilde;uetele, on elektriseadme importija, valmistaja v&otilde;i muul viisil Eestis kasutamiseks &uuml;leandja kohustatud tagastama k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tasu ja h&uuml;vitama inspektsioonile k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud hindamisteenuse tellimisel tehtud kulutused. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If it is established that an electrical equipment does not comply with electrical safety requirements, the importer or manufacturer of the electrical equipment, or the person who transferred the electrical equipment in other manner for use in Estonia is required to return the remuneration specified in subsection (1) of this section and compensate the Inspectorate for costs incurred by ordering the assessment service specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamine ja t&otilde;endamine </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment and Attestation of Conformity </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus </eesti>
<inglise>Approved attestation body </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus on juriidiline isik, kellele majandusminister on andnud &otilde;iguse tegutseda volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutusena. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An approved attestation body is a legal person to which the Minister of Economic Affairs has granted the right to operate as an approved attestation body. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;igus volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutusena tegutsemiseks antakse eraldi igas k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 4 punktides 1-4 loetletud valdkonnas kuni viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The right to operate as an approved attestation body is granted for up to five years separately for each area of activity listed in clauses (4) 1) -4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Majandusminister annab &otilde;iguse tegutseda volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutusena oma k&auml;skkirjaga vastavasisulise taotluse alusel, kui isik vastab volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutusele esitatavatele k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The right to operate as an approved attestation body shall be granted by a directive of the Minister of Economic Affairs on the basis of a corresponding application if the person complies with the requirements established for approved attestation bodies by this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;skkirjas piiritletakse, missuguses ulatuses ja millise kestusega on isikul &otilde;igus tegutseda vastavates valdkondades k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutusena. </eesti>
<inglise>A directive shall define the extent and duration of the right of a person to operate as an approved attestation body on the basis of this Act in the corresponding areas of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Otilde;igus volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutusena tegutsemiseks antakse eraldi j&auml;rgmistes valdkondades: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The right to operate as an approved attestation body shall be granted separately in the following areas of activity: </inglise>
<eesti>1) paragrahvi 5 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud p&auml;devuse hindamine ja p&auml;devustunnistuse v&auml;ljastamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) assessment of competence and issue of certificates of competency specified in subsection 5 (3); </inglise>
<eesti>2) paragrahvi 6 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud elektriseadmete n&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamine ja t&otilde;endamine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) assessment and attestation of conformity of electrical equipment specified in subsection 6 (3); </inglise>
<eesti>3) paragrahvi 9 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud elektripaigaldiste n&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamine ja t&otilde;endamine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) assessment and attestation of conformity of electrical installations specified in subsection 9 (2); </inglise>
<eesti>4) paragrahvi 12 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud elektripaigaldistes korralise kontrolli l&auml;biviimine. </eesti>
<inglise>4) performance of regular inspections of electrical installations specified in subsection 12 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus peab vastama j&auml;rgmistele n&otilde;uetele: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An approved attestation body shall comply with the following requirements: </inglise>
<eesti>1) olema oma hindamis- ja t&otilde;endamistegevuses erapooletu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) be impartial in its assessment and attestation activities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) omama oma hindamis- ja t&otilde;endamistegevuseks vajaliku hariduse ja kogemustega personali, vajalikku tehnilist varustust ning kontrollitegevuse n&otilde;uetekohasust tagavat s&uuml;steemi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) have staff with education and experience necessary for its assessment and attestation activities; have necessary technical equipment, and a system to ensure the conformity of inspection activities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) olema v&otilde;imeline h&uuml;vitama oma tegevusest tuleneda v&otilde;ivaid kahjusid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) be able to compensate for damages which may result from its activities; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vastama volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutusele k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 4 punktides 1-4 nimetatud kindlas valdkonnas tegutsemiseks kehtestatud lisan&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) comply with the additional requirements established for the approved attestation body for operation in particular areas of activity specified in clauses (4) 1) -4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 5 punktis 4 nimetatud lisan&otilde;uded kehtestatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The additional requirements specified in clause (5) 4) of this section shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Hiljemalt kaks kuud enne volituste l&otilde;ppemist v&otilde;ib volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus esitada taotluse volituste pikendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) An approved attestation body may submit an application for the extension of its authority not later than two months prior to the termination of the authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kui volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus vastab talle esitatavatele k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele, pikendab majandusminister volituste kestust kuni viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If an approved attestation body complies with the requirements established for the body by this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof, the Minister of Economic Affairs shall extend the authority of the attestation body for up to five years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutuse kohustused n&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamisel ja t&otilde;endamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of approved attestation bodies in assessment and attestation of conformity </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus tuvastab hinnatava isiku, elektriseadme v&otilde;i -paigaldise v&otilde;i selle k&auml;idu n&otilde;uetekohasuse, v&auml;ljastab ta sellekohase tunnistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) After an approved attestation body has established the compliance of an assessed person, or of an electrical equipment or electrical installation or of the operation thereof with the requirements, the attestation body shall issue a corresponding certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus peab p&otilde;hjendama tunnistuse v&auml;ljastamisest keeldumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An approved attestation body shall justify a refusal to issue a certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus on kohustatud tagama oma hindamis- ja t&otilde;endamistegevuse k&auml;igus saadud &auml;ri- ja tehnikaalase teabe saladuses hoidmise, kui seadused ei n&auml;e ette selle avaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An approved attestation body is required to ensure that the confidentiality of business and technical information which became known to it in the course of assessment or attestation activities is maintained, unless the disclosure of such information is prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus avastab n&otilde;uetekohasuse hindamisel, et elektriseade v&otilde;i -paigaldis ohustab otseselt elu, tervist v&otilde;i vara, peab ta sellest viivitamatult teatama elektriseadme v&otilde;i -paigaldise valdajale ja inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an approved attestation body discovers upon an assessment of conformity that an electrical equipment or electrical installation directly endangers life, health or property, the approved attestation body shall immediately notify the possessor of the electrical equipment or electrical installation and the Inspectorate thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutuse volituste kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of authority of approved attestation body </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus ei vasta talle esitatavatele k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i ei t&auml;ida oma hindamis- ja t&otilde;endamistegevuses talle esitatavaid n&otilde;udeid, m&auml;&auml;rab majandusminister oma k&auml;skkirjaga t&auml;htaja puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks, piirab volituste ulatust v&otilde;i tunnistab volitused kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an approved attestation body does not comply with the requirements established for the body by this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof, or fails to comply with the requirements established for its assessment or attestation activities, the Minister of Economic Affairs shall, by a directive, set a term for the elimination of the deficiencies, restrict the extent of the authority or revoke the authority of the approved attestation body. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puudused pole m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks k&otilde;rvaldatud, piirab majandusminister volituste ulatust v&otilde;i tunnistab volitused kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>If the deficiencies are not eliminated within the specified term, the Minister of Economic Affairs shall restrict the extent of the authority or revoke the authority of the approved attestation body. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volituste kehtetuks tunnistamisel on volitatud t&otilde;endamisasutus kohustatud andma hindamis- ja t&otilde;endamistegevusega seotud dokumentatsiooni &uuml;le majandusministri poolt volitatud isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the authority of an approved attestation body is revoked, the attestation body is required to transfer the documentation concerning the assessment or attestation activities to persons authorised by the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Electrical contractor with right to perform additional inspections </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguse tegutseda lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tjana annab inspektsiooni peadirektor elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tjale oma k&auml;skkirjaga, kui see ettev&otilde;tja vastab kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele, kuni kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right to operate as an electrical contractor with the right to perform additional inspections shall be granted to an electrical contractor by a directive of the Director General of the Inspectorate for up to three years if the contractor complies with the established requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja peab: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An electrical contractor with the right to perform additional inspections shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) olema oma kontrollitegevuses erapooletu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) be impartial in inspection activities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) omama oma kontrollitegevuseks vajaliku hariduse ja kogemustega personali, vajalikku tehnilist varustust ning kontrollitegevuse n&otilde;uetekohasust tagavat s&uuml;steemi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) have staff with education and experience necessary for inspection activities; have necessary technical equipment, and a system to ensure the conformity of inspection activities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) hoidma saladuses oma tegevuse k&auml;igus saadud &auml;ri- ja tehnikaalast teavet, kui seadused ei n&auml;e ette selle avaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) maintain the confidentiality of business and technical information which becomes known to the contractor in the course of its activities, unless the disclosure of such information is prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teatama, olles oma kontrollitegevuse k&auml;igus tuvastanud, et elektriseade v&otilde;i -paigaldis ohustab otseselt elu, tervist v&otilde;i vara, sellest viivitamatult elektriseadme v&otilde;i -paigaldise valdajale ja inspektsioonile; </eesti>
<inglise>4) immediately notify a possessor of an electrical equipment or electrical installation and the Inspectorate if the electrical contractor ascertains in the course of inspection activities that the electrical equipment or electrical installation directly endangers life, health or property; </inglise>
<eesti>5) esitama igal aastal inspektsioonile &uuml;levaate oma kontrollitegevusest. </eesti>
<inglise>5) submit annually overviews of inspection activities to the Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja erapooletusele, personalile, tehnilisele varustusele, kontrollitegevuse n&otilde;uetekohasust tagavale s&uuml;steemile ning kontrollitegevuse &uuml;levaatele esitatavad n&otilde;uded kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The requirements for the impartiality, staff, technical equipment, system ensuring conformity of inspection activities, and for the overviews of inspection activities of electrical contractors with the right to perform additional inspections shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja tuvastab hinnatava elektripaigaldise v&otilde;i selle k&auml;idu n&otilde;uetekohasuse, v&auml;ljastab ta n&otilde;uetekohasust t&otilde;endava dokumendi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) After an electrical contractor with the right to perform additional inspections has established the conformity of an assessed electrical installation or of operation thereof, the electrical contractor shall issue a document attesting conformity. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja peab p&otilde;hjendama n&otilde;uetekohasust t&otilde;endava dokumendi v&auml;ljastamisest keeldumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An electrical contractor with the right to perform additional inspections shall justify a refusal to issue a document attesting conformity. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tja ei t&auml;ida k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud n&otilde;udeid, annab inspektsiooni peadirektor oma k&auml;skkirjaga t&auml;htaja puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks v&otilde;i t&uuml;histab &otilde;iguse tegutseda lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tjana. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If an electrical contractor with the right to perform additional inspections fails to comply with the requirements specified in subsections (2) and (3) of this section, the Director General of the Inspectorate shall, by a directive, set a term for the elimination of the deficiencies or revoke the contractor's right to operate as an electrical contractor with the right to perform additional inspections. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puudusi ei ole t&auml;htajaks k&otilde;rvaldatud, t&uuml;histab inspektsiooni peadirektor &otilde;iguse tegutseda lisakontrolli&otilde;igusega elektrit&ouml;&ouml;de ettev&otilde;tjana. </eesti>
<inglise>If the deficiencies are not eliminated within the term, the Director General of the Inspectorate shall revoke the contractor's right to operate as an electrical contractor with the right to perform additional inspections. </inglise>
